nodes.text: The popultion [sic] has been told for decades that they are simply a culmination of their genes.

Default Conflict

The gene is intellectually dead. Genetic deteminism is intellectually dead. Materialism is intellectually dead. ToE is intellectually dead -- atheism is intellectually dead. The new genetics highlights a paradigm of organic wholeness. We are not a collection of parts. We are a complex wholes, who are able to engage dynamic transformation upon enviornmental and social changes. We are not genetically determined, we are creators of our own destiny. We are no longer a collection of 'things,' we are a collective process.

Its a direct quote from Al Capone in the Kevin Coster version of the Untouchables. None of the alleged deaths have in fact occurred except for genetic determinism which has long been dead so long that there is not even a smell left. And somehow I don't think you will find a proof of GOD in the fact that the genome is more complex than a simplistic point of view such as you apparently held prior to reading some of the newer findings.
Default Conflict

The phrase '#### hits the fan' refers to what would happen if such an event occurred, a big mess.  For example 'Big Jimmy just found out Sly Jones was sleeping with his wife, the #### is really going to hit the fan now!' Substituting something else into the metaphor other than #### renders it meaningless, its unclear what would happen if a 'theory' hit a fan, are you trying to say it would make a mess, that nothing would happen, that it would spin in circles?
I'm glad you made the same correlation I did. ToE is a substitute for #### in this case.

Tsk, tsk same old claims about the death of evolutionary theory based on misreadings of the literature of molecular biology. Nothing new here. Not one bit.

This crushes ToE at the most fundamental level. I've been telling this board for months that the gene is not the player in biological change that everyone thinks it is. The popultion has been told for decades that they are simply a culmination of their genes. How many times have you heard, 'It's in the genes....'???? Not only that but the whole theory of evolution is a result of changes in genes (or alleles). Ha! Now, however, genes are 'losing their glitter.' Now, it's RNA that seems to be 'running the show.' How can it get anymore embarrassing for science that they got the premise wrong for all these years? Why do you think the dude in the article said how 'depressing' all this is? Evolutionists have screwed up in that they have always assumed that the gene is the fundamental unit of life, that complexity goes no further down in the organism and that what determines what or who you are stops at your genes! FALSE! DNA does not dictate who we are, it's the other way around: DNA is just a representative of what we are, where we live, what our social environment is, what our ecological environment is, etc. DNA is not a dictator of life nor does it define us......it's a follower of life and is manipulated by who we are. This reality indeed flips all of biology and ToE on its head. You can deny it all you want -- and I'm sure you will because you have completely brainwashed yourself.   The sun is setting on ToE. Science has lead us astray for decades, and now it's coming back to bite them. What an embarrassment.

Evolutionists have screwed up in that they have always assumed that the gene is the fundamental unit of life, that complexity goes no further down in the organism and that what determines what or who you are stops at your genes! FALSE!

Well, yeah, of course. Put some DNA in a dish and it won't do very much at all; it's not exactly news that the surrounding developmental machinery is significant too. We're just in the process of establishing to what degree that machinery is 'general purpose', and to what degree it encodes specific traits. The rest of your post just goes completely off the rails. Nowhere does the article mention DNA (or anything else for that matter) being designed to suit the purposes of the organism, so I'm not sure why you're getting so excited.
